Observations are where we identify Anthem’s (SWT) which stands for strengths, weaknesses and perceived threats (external) related to the customer’s objectives.  Once the SWT’s are identified, provide the evidence and estimate of impact.  It is important to include internal and external items or trends that may post a unique risk or threat to the client relationship in the next 2-3 years.  

This exercise is not about pointing fingers at anyone, but more around an honest assessment of the state of our relationship and the delivery of our services.  The primary purpose of the exercise is to identify the hurdles that can keep us from helping our clients meet their objectives, and use the effort to figure out what you and your team can do to do address and overcome these hurdles.

 

 - Strength:
   Characteristics of the Account that give it an advantage over competitors.

 - Weakness:  
   Aspects in the Account Relationship that can be used for advancing the relationship and competitive positioning.

 - Threat: 
   Aspects in the Account Relationship that can cause trouble for the relationship.

 

To add or modify the observation, please select the checkbox below:

Note: 

 - Rank [Lowest:1 - Highest:5]
